   <abstract>This paper is a companion document to Promoting Access to Quality Child Care: Critical Steps in Conducting Market Rate Surveys and Establishing Rate Policies, which discusses the concept of market rates and the elements involved in coducting an effective market rate survey. This paper discusses the role of providers, CCR&amp;R agencies, community-based organizatiins, and other advocates in responding to market rate surveys and policies.</abstract>
